{
	"nodes":[
		{"id":"thesis","type":"file","file":"09 - Patterns and Theses/Thesis - Russian Activity Drives Mediterranean Observations.md","x":-200,"y":-700,"width":520,"height":260,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"legend","type":"text","text":"## Russian activity drives Mediterranean observations\n\nThe Eastern Mediterranean cluster of U.S. military UAP observations correlates with ==Russian Navy and aviation activity==, especially the 2015-2017 Russian Syria deployment and recurring KCTG (Kuznetsov Carrier Task Group) operations.\n\n- U.S. P-8A patrols in the Eastern Med were specifically tasked to monitor Russian naval and air activity.\n- Observations cluster along Russian transit routes and near Russian-aligned Syrian airfields.\n- The one well-documented case is assessed in-source as Russian KCTG missile activity.\n\nConfidence: MODERATE. Small sample; strong single case.","x":-1380,"y":-700,"width":660,"height":540,"color":"2"},
		{"id":"hdr-anchor","type":"text","text":"## Anchor case (assessed conventional)","x":-820,"y":-60,"width":420,"height":90,"color":"3"},
